The known distribution is extended from the 
type
locality (whakatane Seamount, 
Bay of Plenty
, 
2672–2776 m
) on the southern Kermadec Ridge, westwards to the Lord Howe Rise and eastern Australian continental slope, and northwards to Monowai Caldera (northern Kermadec Ridge). The bathymetric range is also significantly expanded, with the Monowai Caldera (
640 m
), and Clark Seamount (
927 m
) specimens from the shallowest depths; all others were taken at lower bathyal depths (
1770–3798 m
).
